Dia. 02 Follow up
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black defends against the snapback with 1 then White breaks the eye with 2 and captures Black easily.
\par
\par If Black plays at A instead of 1, White plays at B. Black can't get a sente eye on the right side.
\par
\par }
